#1 History of resected rectal carcinoma with 4 of 21 nodes positive
#2 DVT on anticoagulation
Plan:  I discussed the concept of adjuvant treatment with her.  I explained she could be cured with no additional treatment or even if she took chemotherapy she could still develop a recurrence of her cancer.  In terms of neoadjuvant treatment, she did not tolerate Xeloda, though she was receiving radiation therapy along with this.  She is on Coumadin and restarting Xeloda would create another problem from that standpoint.  As she is on anticoagulation, I am reluctant to put in a Port-A-Cath and consider FOLFOX therapy for her.  Given the choice of whether to take chemotherapy or not, she clearly wants to take it.  I would, therefore, suggest she take the weekly 5-FU, Leucovorin Jackson Regimen for six-months.  Since she lives near Mayville, it would be reasonable for her to receive her treatment there.  I have called the office of Dr. Ernie Hubbard to set-up an appointment for her to be seen by him.  The patient had signed a release for us to send him information.  Hopefully, she will tolerate this treatment without difficulty.  She may wish to return here for follow-up exams or on the other hand she may ultimately decide to continue care in Mayville.  She will let me know later what her wishes are.
We will send a copy of our CT-scan to Dr. Hubbard as a baseline study.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

